      public SavedModelBundle.Exporter withTags(String... tags)
      Sets the set of tags that identify the specific graph in the saved model to save.

      Note that only one graph per model can be saved right now using this API.

      Parameters:
      tags - the tags identifying the specific MetaGraphDef to save.
      Returns:
      this object
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if tags are invalid

    • withFunction

      public SavedModelBundle.Exporter withFunction(SessionFunction function)
      Save a function of this model.

      The function carries a signature (i.e. a list of user-friendly input and outputs names to a graph) and a valid session to a graph to be saved in the model.

      Note:Eventually, TensorFlow for Java will support the export of functions objects like the Python API does but right now, only session-centric models are supported (i.e. models that has a single main graph and one or more signatures). These models are compatible with those exported by TensorFlow 1.x or by TensorFlow 2.x estimators.
      Therefore, all functions exported in a model should share the same session at the moment or an exception will be thrown.       This applies to sessions set via withSession(Session) as well, the exporter can only even have one session.

      Parameters:
      function - a function carrying a signature and a valid session to the graph to be saved
      Returns:
      this object
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if a function with the same name has already been added to the model
      UnsupportedOperationException - if the session is already set to a different session

    • withFunctions

      public SavedModelBundle.Exporter withFunctions(SessionFunction... functions)
      Save multiple functions. Wrapper around withFunction(SessionFunction). All functions must have the same session.
      Parameters:
      functions - the functions to export
      Returns:
      this object
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if a function with the same name has already been added to the model
      UnsupportedOperationException - if the session is already set to a different session
      See Also:
      • withFunction(SessionFunction)

    • withSignature

      public SavedModelBundle.Exporter withSignature(Signature signature)
      Add a signature to the model. This wraps the signature in a SessionFunction using the exporter's already-set session. As such, either withSession(Session) or withFunction(SessionFunction) must be called before this method.
      Returns:
      this
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if no session has been set

    • withSignatures

      public SavedModelBundle.Exporter withSignatures(Signature... signatures)
      Add multiple signatures to the model. Wraps withSignature(Signature)

      Either withSession(Session) or withFunction(SessionFunction) must be called before this method, and the session set there will be used for these signatures.

      Returns:
      this
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if no session has been set
      See Also:
      • withSession(Session)
